name: Prolapse by R.F. Bongarten
description:
“And the heart jumps. It jumps a lot.
Enough failure of joy.
A conversion of dimensions between the expected reality and between what actually happens.
We always hope for one thing. But have you noticed that something else always happens.
It's because things are difficult at all.
And transforming from one form to another. And this work shows a transformation.
Never expect anything ready.
Because it always changes.”

By R.F. Bongarten, brazilian artist.
